## 2. Healthcare Philanthropy Market

### 2.1 Market Size

| Metric | Value | Source |
|--------|-------|--------|
| Nonprofit hospitals (approx.) | ~3,000 | AHA |
| Hospital foundations (approx.) | ~2,500 | AHP estimate |
| Average foundation net fundraising revenue | $7.7M | AHP Report on Giving 2024 |
| Median cost to raise a dollar (CTRD) | $0.22 | AHP 2024 |
| Average ROI per $1 invested | $4.53 | AHP 2024 |
| High performers ROI | $6.36+ | AHP 2024 |

### 2.2 Healthcare vs. Higher Ed Comparison

| Factor | Higher Education | Healthcare |
|--------|-----------------|------------|
| Donor Type | Alumni (lifetime relationship) | Grateful patients (episodic) |
| Regulatory | FERPA | HIPAA (more restrictive) |
| Donor Pipeline | Built-in (graduates) | Requires identification |
| Cultivation Cycle | Years (student → donor) | Shorter (gratitude-based) |
| Data Challenges | Fragmented CRMs | PHI restrictions |
| Technology Stack | Blackbaud/Salesforce dominant | More fragmented |

### 2.3 Key Insight

Healthcare philanthropy has strong ROI economics but faces unique challenges. HIPAA compliance and grateful patient identification require specialized capabilities. Most hospital foundations use the same CRM vendors (Blackbaud, Salesforce) but with healthcare-specific configurations.

