## 3. General Nonprofit Market

### 3.1 Universe Size

| Metric | Value | Source |
|--------|-------|--------|
| Total nonprofits (all types) | ~1.8M | IRS/Candid |
| 501(c)(3) public charities | ~1.4M | IRS |
| Revenue >$10M | ~50,000 | Estimated |
| Revenue >$1M | ~250,000 | Estimated |
| Revenue $250K–$1M | ~300,000 | Estimated |

### 3.2 Technology Adoption

| Capability | Adoption Rate | Source |
|-----------|--------------|--------|
| Any fundraising software | ~60% | Industry surveys |
| Formal CRM | ~40% | Industry surveys |
| Wealth screening | ~25% | Industry estimate |
| AI tools in operations | ~30% | TechSoup 2025 |
| Smart donation forms | 4% | Nonprofit Tech for Good |

**Key Insight:** General nonprofits represent a massive market by volume but a fragmented one. Most organizations under $1M revenue lack formal major gift programs. The TAM is large but the SAM for sophisticated analytics is concentrated in the top 50,000–100,000 organizations.

